    "Training Strategy": "The loss function is a weighted sum: Loss = lambda_pde * MSE(PDE_residual) + lambda_ic * MSE(IC_error) + lambda_bc * MSE(BC_error). Collocation points are sampled using Latin Hypercube Sampling (LHS) to ensure domain coverage. Optimization uses Adam for initial global search followed by L-BFGS for precise convergence. Adaptive loss weighting is recommended to balance the PDE residual against data constraints.",
